Whether arcane, divine, or psionic, magical items carry their magic within. Yet magical equipment is still affected by dimensional relations and spell alterations, particularly any which simulate spells. Take a }{\i\f30\fs20 ring of invisibility }{
\f30\fs20 to a plane where illusion spells do not function and the ring won\rquote t work either. More importantly, some magical items may attract attention from the natives of 
a plane. An unholy weapon brought onto the Upper Planes is a beacon of evil to the celestials and deities there. Spells or equipment that can be used to hide magical auras are especially useful when carrying such items.
